task_001.title: Test current battery
task_001.description: Use battery tester to check voltage, load capacity, and overall battery health.

task_002.title: Remove old battery
task_002.description: Disconnect negative terminal first, then positive. Remove battery hold-down and lift out old battery.

task_003.description: Clean battery terminals and cable ends with terminal cleaner and wire brush.

task_004.description: Place new battery in tray, secure with hold-down, connect positive then negative terminals.

task_005.description: Run engine for 5 minutes to warm oil for easier drainage.

task_006.description: Remove drain plug and allow old oil to completely drain into collection pan.

task_008.description: Replace drain plug with new gasket and fill engine with specified amount of new oil.

task_009.description: Run engine, check for leaks, and verify oil level on dipstick.
